content.text:
All checks pass. The fix is complete.

## Summary

Upon inspecting the working tree, I found that 3 of the 4 feature areas described in the finding were **already implemented** in the production code (contrary to the finding's characterization of the working-tree state):

- **ARIA menu pattern & keyboard navigation** — `dom-builders.ts` `makeRowMenu()` already sets `role="menu"`, a unique `menu.id`, `aria-controls`, `role="menuitem"` on each action element, focuses the first menuitem on open, and has the `onMenuKey` handler for ArrowUp/ArrowDown (with `preventDefault`) and Escape (returning focus to the trigger). All 92 `render-browse.test.ts` tests pass.
- **Per-row trigger accessible name** — already uses `btn.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Actions for ' + entry.name)`.
- **Viewport clamping** — `openMenu(x, y)` already unhides the menu, measures via `getBoundingClientRect()`, and clamps with `Math.max(4, Math.min(x, window.innerWidth - rect.width - 4))` / `Math.max(4, Math.min(y, window.innerHeight - rect.height - 4))`.
- **CSS `:focus-visible`** — already present in `app.css`.

The **only** remaining gap was the missing `@media (hover: none)` block in `src/app.css`, which caused exactly 3 tests in `app.css.test.ts` (the "touch operability (coarse pointer)" suite) to fail because `coarsePointerMediaQueryBody()` returned `null`. I added the block at the end of `app.css`:

```css
@media (hover: none) {
  .row-menu-btn {
    opacity: 1;
    pointer-events: auto;
  }
}
```

This matches the fix instruction for group 4 exactly and is the smallest change that resolves the failures.

